inlineContent.text: protocol is a convenience protocol that adopts all of the protocols used to handle call-related intents. When your app adopts all of the protocols associated with call handling, you can adopt this one protocol instead of adopting the
An object that adopts this protocol must be able to respond to the following intents:
, a request to search for an entry in the app’s call logs.
, a request to start an audio-only call.
,  a request to start a video call.

Your handler object must be prepared to resolve any parameters associated with these intents and to confirm and handle the requests. When confirming and handling a request, you provide the response object that matches the specified intent.
